<section id="intro">
    <h2>Introduction to Agroforestry</h2>
    <div class="box">
        <p>
            Agroforestry is an integrated land-use management system where trees or shrubs are grown
            together with agricultural crops and/or livestock on the same land. This system helps in
            maintaining ecological balance while improving farm productivity and farmer income.
        </p>

        <p>
            Agroforestry plays an important role in soil conservation, climate change mitigation,
            biodiversity conservation, and sustainable rural development. It reduces soil erosion,
            improves soil fertility, and provides multiple products like timber, fruits, fodder,
            and fuelwood.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="image-row">
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500595046743-cd271d694d30" alt="Agroforestry Field">
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500530855697-b586d89ba3ee" alt="Farm with Trees">
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1592982537447-6f2a6a94a2c3" alt="Sustainable Farming">
    </div>
</section>

<section id="components">
    <h2>Components of Agroforestry</h2>

    <div class="box">
        <b>1. Trees and Shrubs:</b> Neem, Mango, Teak, Eucalyptus, Acacia.
    </div>

    <div class="box">
        <b>2. Agricultural Crops:</b> Wheat, Maize, Pulses, Millets, Oilseeds.
    </div>

    <div class="box">
        <b>3. Livestock (Optional):</b> Cattle, Goats, Sheep, Poultry.
    </div>

    <div class="image-row">
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1589923188900-85dae523342b" alt="Neem Tree">
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1592982537447-6f2a6a94a2c3" alt="Wheat Field">
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1598133894006-3f93c5de0873" alt="Cattle Grazing">
    </div>
</section>

<section id="types">
    <h2>Types of Agroforestry Systems</h2>

    <div class="box">
        <b>1. Agri-silviculture:</b> Trees + Crops  
        Example: Eucalyptus with Wheat or Maize.
    </div>

    <div class="box">
        <b>2. Silvi-pastoral:</b> Trees + Pasture + Animals  
        Example: Trees with grasses for cattle grazing.
    </div>

    <div class="box">
        <b>3. Agri-silvi-pastoral:</b> Trees + Crops + Animals together.
    </div>

    <div class="box">
        <b>4. Horti-silviculture:</b> Fruit trees + Forest trees  
        Example: Mango + Teak plantation.
    </div>

    <div class="image-row">
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500382017468-9049fed747ef" alt="Row Cropping">
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1589923188900-85dae523342b" alt="Silvopastoral System">
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500382017468-9049fed747ef" alt="Mango Orchard">
    </div>
</section>

<section id="benefits">
    <h2>Benefits of Agroforestry</h2>

    <div class="box">
        <b>Economic Benefits:</b>  
        - Provides timber, fruits, fuelwood, and fodder.  
        - Increases farmer income.  
        - Reduces risk of crop failure.
    </div>

    <div class="box">
        <b>Environmental Benefits:</b>  
        - Prevents soil erosion.  
        - Improves soil fertility.  
        - Increases carbon storage (reduces global warming).  
        - Conserves biodiversity.
    </div>

    <div class="box">
        <b>Social Benefits:</b>  
        - Provides employment.  
        - Improves rural livelihood.  
        - Ensures food and fodder security.
    </div>
</section>

<section id="importance">
    <h2>Importance of Agroforestry in India</h2>

    <div class="box">
        <p>
            Agroforestry is highly important in India due to increasing population and demand for food,
            fuel, and timber. It supports sustainable agriculture and helps in climate resilience.
        </p>

        <p>
            The Government of India promotes agroforestry through various schemes and programs to
            support farmers, improve soil health, and increase rural income.
        </p>
    </div>

